March 2nd to May 14th ... every single day is a struggle with me and food. It probably shouldn't be, but we all have our shit. Not a huge difference here by any means, but a difference nonetheless.

Ive tried a few different approaches... but started to realize my biggest issue wasnt, what I was eating, macros vs. keto etc... it was how much I STRESSED MYSELF OUT over EATING... the constant battle of counting everything, weighing this and reducing this and that... first off, thats no way to live ... not for me anyway. Secondly, I would like to enjoy my life, I enjoy socializing and having fun and having WINE at night winding down with my hubby to be. I like grabbing a latte with my girlfriends and sneaking a piece of pizza when the guys leave leftovers at the gym 😛  I love s'mores and rice krispy squares and eating Nutella straight up with a spoon. 
Sure, my results wont be as quick and I wont get that 'six pack' Ive always wanted, but learning to be "OK" with that is a much better feeling mentally and emotionally than knocking myself down, beating myself up or refusing to spend time with friends and family because I "cant eat/drink" things and the thought of the situation is just too much.

So, why this post?

Well, its easier said than done, but what Id like to do is continue to keep a positive and more healthy mindset about myself. Continuing to be healthy, rather than crazy over food. To see how just making better choices on a daily basis rather than obsessing over every single choice - will positively affect my progress and results, not just physically but mentally and emotionally as well. I want to focus more on the energy going into my body to fuel my workouts so I feel strong and beautiful without being negative in the mind. 
Hopefully, putting it out there, to have others hold me accountable & to maybe help someone else who's dealing with the same shit. I know I'm certainly not alone

Lets see how it goes.
